2 spaces for student learning.
3 B. 1. A public school district seeking a grant to establish a
4 phone-free space in a middle school, junior high school, or high
5 school site shall apply to the State Board of Education in the
6 manner and on a form prescribed by the Board. The Board shall
7 prioritize school districts that submit an application by July 1,
8 2025. Any applications received after July 1, 2025, shall be
9 considered on a first come, first served basis.
10 2. After reviewing the applications submitted, the Board shall
11 attempt to select recipients equally from each of the following
12 criteria:
13 a. middle schools, junior high schools, and high schools,
14 that each have an average daily membership (ADM) of
15 fewer than five hundred (500) students,
16 b. middle schools, junior high schools, and high schools,
17 that each have an ADM of five hundred (500) or more
18 students but fewer than one thousand five hundred
19 (1,500) students, and
20 c. middle schools, junior high schools, and high schools,
21 that each have an ADM of one thousand five hundred
22 (1,500) or more students.
23 3. When selecting grant recipients pursuant to this subsection,
24 the Board shall attempt to select a variety of schools which are
